WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.259 --> 00:00:11.678
[ Tires screech ]

2
00:00:09.259 --> 00:00:11.678
[ Crashing ]

3
00:00:17.726 --> 00:00:20.145
[ Flare sizzles ]

4
00:00:20.187 --> 00:00:22.564
[ Clattering ]

5
00:00:23.899 --> 00:00:26.401
[ "57 Coupe de Ville" plays ]

6
00:00:26.485 --> 00:00:31.281
{\an8}♪♪

7
00:00:31.323 --> 00:00:33.867
♪ Well. everybody loves me ♪

8
00:00:33.951 --> 00:00:35.410
♪ Everywhere I go ♪

9
00:00:35.494 --> 00:00:37.454
♪ The women wanna kiss me ♪

10
00:00:37.496 --> 00:00:39.373
♪ The men all wanna know ♪

11
00:00:37.496 --> 00:00:39.373
[ Spits ]

12
00:00:39.456 --> 00:00:40.832
♪ How's my baby handle ♪

13
00:00:39.456 --> 00:00:40.832
[ Engine starts ]

14
00:00:40.916 --> 00:00:44.753
♪ When I take her up
to Blueberry Hill?

15
00:00:44.836 --> 00:00:46.463
[ Air hisses ]

16
00:00:46.505 --> 00:00:48.507
♪ I tell ‘em
life’s a bowl of cherries ♪

17
00:00:48.590 --> 00:00:52.094
♪ In my ‘57 Coupe de Ville ♪

18
00:00:53.804 --> 00:00:55.681
[ Music stops ]

19
00:00:55.764 --> 00:00:58.016
[ Wind howling ]

20
00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:01.103
[ Exhales sharply ]

21
00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:12.906
[ Engine shuts off ]

22
00:01:12.990 --> 00:01:15.033
[ Muzak playing ]

23
00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:17.327
[ Bowling pins clatter ]

24
00:01:20.455 --> 00:01:22.583
There he is.
Knew I'd get a handsome man

25
00:01:22.666 --> 00:01:24.209
in here if I waited around
long enough.

26
00:01:24.293 --> 00:01:26.211
Had to patch a tire
out on County Line.

27
00:01:26.295 --> 00:01:28.297
Too good for a tow?

28
00:01:26.295 --> 00:01:28.297
Too impatient.

29
00:01:28.338 --> 00:01:31.300
You city folk.
Always in a hurry.

30
00:01:31.383 --> 00:01:33.051
By God. look who it is!

31
00:01:33.135 --> 00:01:34.720
He's back!

32
00:01:33.135 --> 00:01:34.720
Hey!

33
00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:36.221
Welcome back. brother!

34
00:01:36.305 --> 00:01:37.514
Don't know why I ever leave.

35
00:01:37.556 --> 00:01:39.391
A place to bowl.
a place to fish.

36
00:01:39.433 --> 00:01:42.436
Together:
And a beer to hold doing it!

37
00:01:42.519 --> 00:01:44.021
[ Burps ]

38
00:01:42.519 --> 00:01:44.021
[ Laughter ]

39
00:01:44.062 --> 00:01:45.105
Best friends!

40
00:01:45.188 --> 00:01:46.315
We love you. Ted!

41
00:01:46.398 --> 00:01:48.108
Together: Ted!

42
00:01:48.191 --> 00:01:56.074
{\an8}♪♪

43
00:01:56.116 --> 00:02:03.749
{\an8}♪♪

44
00:02:03.790 --> 00:02:12.049
{\an8}♪♪

45
00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:19.973
{\an8}♪♪

46
00:02:20.057 --> 00:02:22.267
{\an8}You still selling PVC?

47
00:02:22.351 --> 00:02:23.602
{\an8}How’s -- How’s
business down there?

48
00:02:23.685 --> 00:02:25.187
{\an8}Good enough
to get me back up here.

49
00:02:25.270 --> 00:02:26.438
{\an8}Think you could put in
a word?

50
00:02:26.521 --> 00:02:28.398
{\an8}Son. you don't wanna
sell pipe.

51
00:02:28.440 --> 00:02:29.858
{\an8}He just wants to lay some.

52
00:02:29.941 --> 00:02:31.193
{\an8}[ Laughter ]

53
00:02:31.234 --> 00:02:33.362
{\an8}Ah. good to have you back.
brother.

54
00:02:33.445 --> 00:02:35.280
{\an8}Ahhh. Split a sixer?

55
00:02:35.322 --> 00:02:37.407
{\an8}[ Engines starting ]

56
00:02:37.449 --> 00:02:39.534
{\an8}Marjorie's keeping the place
open late now?

57
00:02:39.576 --> 00:02:42.037
{\an8}Yeah. Her mother passed
a few months back.

58
00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:43.455
{\an8}Don't think
she wants to go home.

59
00:02:43.538 --> 00:02:45.707
{\an8}Everybody's runnin'
from something.

60
00:02:45.749 --> 00:02:47.793
{\an8}[ Gearshift clicks ]

61
00:02:49.419 --> 00:02:50.754
{\an8}[ Door opens. bottles clink ]

62
00:02:50.796 --> 00:02:52.839
{\an8}How's Luisa?
She still kick you out of bed

63
00:02:52.923 --> 00:02:54.007
{\an8}when you drink?

64
00:02:52.923 --> 00:02:54.007
{\an8}Yep.

65
00:02:54.091 --> 00:02:55.676
{\an8}Might as well
keep drinking.

66
00:02:55.759 --> 00:02:57.469
[ Both laugh ]

67
00:02:57.552 --> 00:03:01.098
Open the register
and gimme your wallet!

68
00:02:57.552 --> 00:03:01.098
[ Gasps ]

69
00:03:01.139 --> 00:03:02.265
Ahh!

70
00:03:02.307 --> 00:03:04.476
No. no. no.

71
00:03:06.478 --> 00:03:08.021
[ Robber groans ]

72
00:03:08.105 --> 00:03:09.690
[ Breathing heavily ]

73
00:03:09.773 --> 00:03:10.982
[ Clattering ]

74
00:03:11.066 --> 00:03:12.109
Teddy?

75
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:13.610
{\an8}Hello.
There's a robbery.

76
00:03:13.652 --> 00:03:15.445
{\an8}I think this guy's having
a heart attack.

77
00:03:15.487 --> 00:03:17.489
{\an8}[ Bells ring ]

78
00:03:15.487 --> 00:03:17.489
{\an8}Ted. where you going?

79
00:03:17.531 --> 00:03:19.700
{\an8}Hey!
The cops are coming.

80
00:03:19.783 --> 00:03:21.034
Ted! Teddy!

81
00:03:21.118 --> 00:03:23.161
This guy's dying in here!

82
00:03:23.203 --> 00:03:25.539
[ Electricity humming ]

83
00:03:39.636 --> 00:03:40.762
Ahh!

84
00:03:40.846 --> 00:03:42.347
Gaaah!

85
00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:43.849
Alright. well. shit.

86
00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:43.849
What the hell?
What the hell?!

87
00:03:43.932 --> 00:03:46.560
Looks like you learned
some things about your body.

88
00:03:46.643 --> 00:03:48.061
I'll make this simple. Ted.

89
00:03:48.145 --> 00:03:50.564
You're not a PVC salesman
from two states south.

90
00:03:50.647 --> 00:03:52.274
You're the smartest man
who's ever lived.

91
00:03:52.357 --> 00:03:54.192
and you were born
400 lightyears away.

92
00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:55.902
{\an8}You’re on Beloi-6E.

93
00:03:55.986 --> 00:03:57.863
{\an8}It's a primitive planet
with good country music

94
00:03:57.904 --> 00:04:00.741
{\an8}and a shit-ton of snow.
real early '90s Earth vibes.

95
00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:02.492
{\an8}They're 100 years
from first contact.

96
00:04:02.534 --> 00:04:04.953
{\an8}so they don't know who I am --
who <i>you</i> are.

97
00:04:05.036 --> 00:04:06.288
{\an8}Which is the whole point.

98
00:04:06.371 --> 00:04:08.081
{\an8}Y-You think it's fun
to be a god. Ted?

99
00:04:08.165 --> 00:04:10.876
{\an8}You think God's nipples get hard
when he murders a fish?

100
00:04:10.959 --> 00:04:12.169
{\an8}Th-That's why every summer

101
00:04:12.210 --> 00:04:13.712
{\an8}I take two weeks off
and come here.

102
00:04:13.754 --> 00:04:16.757
{\an8}I wipe my brain and pull all
but my survival tech.

103
00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:19.509
[ Groaning ]

104
00:04:19.551 --> 00:04:21.720
{\an8}I go home with the peace
of mind stupid people get

105
00:04:21.762 --> 00:04:23.638
{\an8}from watching Kevin Costner
movies.

106
00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:26.558
{\an8}So. look. if you're seeing this
because shit's gone sideways.

107
00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:28.226
{\an8}hit the red button
to be me again.

108
00:04:28.310 --> 00:04:29.978
{\an8}If everything's cool.
hit the blue button

109
00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:32.355
{\an8}to clear this from your memory
and enjoy the rest of your trip.

110
00:04:32.397 --> 00:04:33.815
{\an8}Okay. Morty. that’s a wrap on

111
00:04:33.899 --> 00:04:35.567
{\an8}"If you’ve been
messing with my tech."

112
00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:37.903
{\an8}Let's run
the "Taken" scenarios.

113
00:04:38.487 --> 00:04:40.906
[ Groaning ]

114
00:04:41.823 --> 00:04:43.074
[ Gasps ]

115
00:04:43.158 --> 00:04:45.452
[ Breathing heavily ]

116
00:04:47.245 --> 00:04:49.331
[ Electricity zaps ]

117
00:04:54.419 --> 00:04:57.005
You here about
the dishwasher job?

118
00:04:57.088 --> 00:04:59.591
Shit. you're a popsicle.

119
00:05:03.345 --> 00:05:06.264
You know me. right?

120
00:05:06.348 --> 00:05:09.434
[ Chuckles ]
I'd sure like to think so.

121
00:05:09.476 --> 00:05:10.894
I mean it.
How could you?

122
00:05:10.936 --> 00:05:13.480
I'm just some guy
who shows up every year.

123
00:05:13.563 --> 00:05:16.399
Well. something keeps you
coming back here.

124
00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:18.902
Ooh! Lay back.
I got a surprise for you.

125
00:05:20.111 --> 00:05:22.280
Got this set up
since your last visit.

126
00:05:22.364 --> 00:05:24.199
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

127
00:05:24.282 --> 00:05:25.617
It's nice.

128
00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:27.619
Haven't really found occasion
to use it.

129
00:05:27.661 --> 00:05:29.454
Thanks for giving me one.

130
00:05:29.496 --> 00:05:31.790
I don't mind the company.

131
00:05:32.958 --> 00:05:34.793
You still have
that spare room in back?

132
00:05:34.876 --> 00:05:37.087
I don't want to sleep
in the RV.

133
00:05:37.128 --> 00:05:46.638
{\an8}♪♪

134
00:05:48.223 --> 00:05:50.809
Mm. Don't go.

135
00:05:50.892 --> 00:05:53.061
I'm not gonna.

136
00:06:00.151 --> 00:06:01.903
[ Door opens ]

137
00:06:01.987 --> 00:06:04.614
Okay. obviously.
you're seeing <i>this</i> hologram

138
00:06:04.656 --> 00:06:07.242
because you ignored the
instructions from the last one.

139
00:06:07.284 --> 00:06:09.995
If you’re seeing this hologram.
you decided to ignore...

140
00:06:07.284 --> 00:06:09.995
I dunno why
that would’ve happened.

141
00:06:10.036 --> 00:06:11.413
it’d mean
you went pretty rogue.

142
00:06:10.036 --> 00:06:11.413
...the hologram
that’s currently playing.

143
00:06:11.496 --> 00:06:12.831
So just a gentle reminder --

144
00:06:12.914 --> 00:06:14.541
you’re not a real person.
you’re me.

145
00:06:14.624 --> 00:06:16.543
You’re permanently...your
vacation spot.

146
00:06:16.626 --> 00:06:18.169
which hurts you more
than it hurts me.

147
00:06:18.253 --> 00:06:20.964
Though. in all honesty.
we’re both getting hurt

148
00:06:21.006 --> 00:06:23.425
pretty severely...

149
00:06:25.302 --> 00:06:26.761
[ Laughter ]

150
00:06:26.845 --> 00:06:28.889
Ted. one of these days.
you gotta come up in July.

151
00:06:28.972 --> 00:06:32.183
I caught a muskie last summer
came about up to my neck.

152
00:06:32.267 --> 00:06:34.185
Stop lying to the man.

153
00:06:32.267 --> 00:06:34.185
No fish in this lake.

154
00:06:34.227 --> 00:06:36.354
Actually. thought
I might stick around this year.

155
00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:38.231
See the thaw.

156
00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:38.231
For real. Teddy?

157
00:06:38.315 --> 00:06:39.649
You're gonna --
You're gonna stay?

158
00:06:39.691 --> 00:06:41.067
What about your company?

159
00:06:41.151 --> 00:06:42.777
Doesn't seem real.

160
00:06:42.819 --> 00:06:45.989
I-It's like I've been pretending
I go somewhere when I leave.

161
00:06:46.031 --> 00:06:48.867
but I think I only exist
when I'm here.

162
00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:52.621
Like this is literally the
only place I'm actually alive.

163
00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:55.832
Does that...make sense?

164
00:06:55.874 --> 00:06:58.001
Good thing
nobody's driving tonight.

165
00:06:58.043 --> 00:07:00.712
{\an8}[ Laughter ]

166
00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:02.881
{\an8}[ Water splashes. reel squeals ]

167
00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:02.881
{\an8}Hey!

168
00:07:02.964 --> 00:07:05.717
[ Snoring ]

169
00:07:10.263 --> 00:07:12.807
[ Whirring ]

170
00:07:12.891 --> 00:07:20.857
{\an8}♪♪

171
00:07:20.899 --> 00:07:23.944
[ Ringing ]

172
00:07:24.027 --> 00:07:26.571
Rick: Fuck me.

173
00:07:26.655 --> 00:07:28.365
Morty: <i>Hello? Rick? Rick!</i>

174
00:07:26.655 --> 00:07:28.365
Who is this?

175
00:07:28.406 --> 00:07:29.866
<i>Aaawwww. I’m really gonna
get in trouble for this.</i>

176
00:07:29.908 --> 00:07:31.743
How are you calling
my leg?

177
00:07:31.826 --> 00:07:33.244
<i>I’m not supposed to ever
use the leg phone.</i>

178
00:07:33.286 --> 00:07:35.246
<i>but I-I just need you
to get in the egg.</i>

179
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.999
<i>Don't pick a fight
with yourself. okay?</i>

180
00:07:38.041 --> 00:07:40.043
<i>I just want to get you home
before anything worse happens.</i>

181
00:07:40.085 --> 00:07:42.754
Nothing's worse than
finding out I'm some character

182
00:07:42.837 --> 00:07:45.173
that asshole plays.
some costume he puts on to --

183
00:07:45.256 --> 00:07:47.342
<i>He doesn’t need you alive
to bring you home.</i>

184
00:07:47.425 --> 00:07:49.219
It's not my home!
I'm not him!

185
00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:51.471
<i>You are.
I mean. I agree with you.</i>

186
00:07:51.554 --> 00:07:54.224
<i>He can be kind of a dick.
but y'know. this --</i>

187
00:07:54.265 --> 00:07:55.892
<i>this is just how it is.</i>

188
00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:57.602
No! Help!

189
00:07:57.686 --> 00:08:00.105
Help!

190
00:07:57.686 --> 00:08:00.105
<i>Oh. and if you could just
hang up the leg phone?</i>

191
00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:01.606
<i>I’ll just -- I’ll never
hear the end of it</i>

192
00:08:01.648 --> 00:08:03.441
<i>if the leg phone gets lost.</i>

193
00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:05.276
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

194
00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:07.070
[ Groaning ]

195
00:08:09.739 --> 00:08:11.282
Ted. are you okay?

196
00:08:11.324 --> 00:08:12.701
[ Groans ] Thank you.

197
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:14.369
What is this thing. Ted?

198
00:08:14.452 --> 00:08:16.121
I'm not who you think I am.

199
00:08:16.162 --> 00:08:19.290
Is this your ship
from space?

200
00:08:19.374 --> 00:08:20.875
Your spaceship?

201
00:08:20.959 --> 00:08:22.127
It's his.

202
00:08:22.210 --> 00:08:24.129
He's...non-vacation me.

203
00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:26.464
I don't know him.
And I don't want to.

204
00:08:26.548 --> 00:08:27.924
But this asshole's
coming for me

205
00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:30.051
and I don't intend
to let him win.

206
00:08:30.135 --> 00:08:31.928
Marjorie:
For the love of Pete.

207
00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:33.763
Do you understand
what you're asking?

208
00:08:33.805 --> 00:08:36.224
I wouldn't ask at all
if there were any other way.

209
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:40.645
<i>Janice. Mary.
I gotta send you home.</i>

210
00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:41.938
<i>We're closing early.</i>

211
00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:45.650
Come on!

212
00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:45.650
We're only three frames in!

213
00:08:45.692 --> 00:08:47.485
[ Switches clicking ]

214
00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:49.654
Thank you.

215
00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:49.654
[ Muttering ]

216
00:08:49.738 --> 00:08:51.698
Nobody gonna
take me seriously.

217
00:08:51.781 --> 00:08:53.700
Janice’s gonna
have her word...

218
00:08:53.783 --> 00:08:56.286
Promise me you won't
come back here tonight.

219
00:08:56.327 --> 00:08:58.121
Always were dramatic.

220
00:08:58.163 --> 00:08:59.998
Promise.

221
00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:03.418
I just -- Don't die
in my bowling alley.

222
00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:05.670
You hear me?

223
00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:09.007
[ Groans ]

224
00:09:09.090 --> 00:09:11.092
[ Grunting ]

225
00:09:11.176 --> 00:09:12.510
Holy hell.

226
00:09:12.552 --> 00:09:14.220
How's it going out there.
Bowser?

227
00:09:14.304 --> 00:09:15.847
Bowser: All good.

228
00:09:18.349 --> 00:09:19.476
Sprinklers. Antonio?

229
00:09:19.517 --> 00:09:21.186
Working on it.
Little Mike?

230
00:09:21.269 --> 00:09:23.313
[ Valves squeaking ]

231
00:09:23.354 --> 00:09:25.190
[ Remote beeps ]

232
00:09:25.231 --> 00:09:27.025
Okay. Big Mike.

233
00:09:27.067 --> 00:09:28.193
[ Saw buzzing ]

234
00:09:28.234 --> 00:09:30.236
[ Rick screams ]

235
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:32.781
[ Electricity humming ]

236
00:09:34.574 --> 00:09:36.826
[ Whoosh ]

237
00:09:37.702 --> 00:09:40.747
[ Whirring ]

238
00:09:42.916 --> 00:09:44.375
[ Drones buzzing ]

239
00:09:44.417 --> 00:09:46.586
Now!

240
00:09:55.845 --> 00:09:58.848
We need those sprinklers.
Antonio!

241
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:01.309
It's not working.

242
00:10:01.392 --> 00:10:02.519
There's too many!

243
00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:04.771
Fry 'em!

244
00:10:08.149 --> 00:10:09.984
Mike!

245
00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:13.404
Follow me.
ya drone bastards!

246
00:10:14.447 --> 00:10:16.032
Whoa!

247
00:10:17.784 --> 00:10:19.327
Teddy. drop!

248
00:10:19.410 --> 00:10:20.787
[ Fire alarm rings ]

249
00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:22.914
[ Electronic whirring ]

250
00:10:26.501 --> 00:10:28.002
-Yes!
-Come on! Rack' em up!

251
00:10:28.086 --> 00:10:29.629
-Whoo-hoo!
-Time for a beer!

252
00:10:29.712 --> 00:10:31.756
Fuck you.
you self-centered prick!

253
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:34.259
Who's not a real person now.
huh?

254
00:10:37.595 --> 00:10:39.347
Marjorie!

255
00:10:39.430 --> 00:10:40.849
Why'd you come back?

256
00:10:40.932 --> 00:10:42.767
I told you not to come back.

257
00:10:42.851 --> 00:10:44.519
You know me. [ Coughs ]

258
00:10:44.602 --> 00:10:46.855
I'm a stubborn old bitch.

